g.title: EleanorRank2Convo1 begins.
g.text: EleanorRank2Convo1 begins.

g.title: j1593971276
g.text: Are you as sick as Lettie seems to think you are?

g.title: j648843880
g.text: How’s your personal Infestation going?

g.title: j335636620
g.text: What’s the deal with you and Lettie?

g.title: j3680757851
g.text: Let’s get this straight. Lettie doesn’t think I’m sick. Lettie thinks I’m a demon.

g.title: j2155479090
g.text: It’s not unpleasant, which is more than you can say for most parasitic infestations.

g.title: j4086656429
g.text: Have you heard what she calls me?

g.title: j1255340905
g.text: I wonder what it’s like to have such a romantic view of the world. You’d think a medic would deal in measurable facts. Ten CC of this, identify the microbes of that.

g.title: j3377382433
g.text: I can feel the Technocytes swimming in my blood. If I close my eyes I can see sparkles like fairy dust.

g.title: j3029527461
g.text: Honestly, no.

g.title: j2123242761
g.text: ‘La Bruja Metiche’. The nosy witch.

g.title: j4058514395
g.text: Very scientific of you. I thought you believed in more spiritual things?

g.title: j2076900987
g.text: Sounds like you think the ‘loss of humanity’ part is exaggerated.

g.title: j1134559761
g.text: It means me well. Can you understand that?

g.title: j2240994554
g.text: ‘La Bruja Metiche’. The nosy witch. I suppose she could do far worse, considering her vocabulary and flair for creative obscenities.

g.title: j2090400647
g.text: Yep. She sits there smirking with her phials and potions, her bottles of blood and slivers of skin, her army of ratty familiars skittering all over the place, and she has the temerity to call ME a witch.

g.title: j64719451
g.text: Well, yes. Living the way we do, how could one not believe in the spiritual world?

g.title: j3482601757
g.text: I’m still Eleanor Nightingale. That’s more important to me than being ‘human’ is.

g.title: j2141558215
g.text: Everything it does, it does out of a sincere wish to fix me up and make me better. If I’m quick and lethal and hard to kill, I’ll be a good host. So it fulfills its part of our symbiotic bargain by giving me shark skin and wolf fangs, along with a tongue like a leather whip.

g.title: j2765413087
g.text: I have heard her tell Quincy to do some rather inventive things with playground fixtures and parts of his anatomy that left me chuckling over the visual for some time, I must admit.

g.title: j384988185
g.text: I get it, you don’t like each other.

g.title: j2287450395
g.text: Has it always been this way between you?

g.title: j1241501588
g.text: She thinks you’ll lose control.

g.title: j2546009719
g.text: Check boolean EleanorVoidLove

g.title: j949913260
g.text: I’ve seen what human beings are capable of. We’re not special. In fact, going by what I’ve seen in your head, we get even worse over time.

g.title: j3082902979
g.text: Yet she sits there smirking with her phials and potions, her bottles of blood and slivers of skin, her army of ratty familiars skittering all over the place, and she has the temerity to call ME a witch.

g.title: j1624291693
g.text: Don’t get me wrong. I WOULD piss on her if she was on fire.

g.title: j646997697
g.text: I think you can guess the answer to that.

g.title: j2319061131
g.text: I know. Sometimes I do, too. I have a recurring nightmare where I rip her throat out just as she puts a bullet through my heart.

g.title: j2844938039
g.text: The Void is proof positive that the spiritual is just as real as the material. All your people have done, aside from putting a different name on it, is develop a reliable means of getting there and back.

g.title: j2546009719->j2844938039
g.text: true

g.title: j1259132086
g.text: Listen. Just because I admit the existence of demonic forces doesn’t mean I’m content to be written off as one.

g.title: j2546009719->j1259132086
g.text: false

g.title: j42144458
g.text: Check boolean EleanorEntrati

g.title: j1011446098
g.text: But I’d take my time over it.

g.title: Chat ends.
g.text: Chat ends.

g.title: j3759804134
g.text: But being afraid of something doesn’t make it real. So far I have gone on zero bloody rampages. ZERO.

g.title: j391308599
g.text: What’s happening in my system is the result of quite mundane atoms and molecules waltzing together in unexpected and remarkable ways. Any spiritual significance to that will be imparted by me. Not Lettie.

g.title: j3189330905
g.text: You want to just give up? You sound like Son.

g.title: j42144458->j3189330905
g.text: true

g.title: j3510904057
g.text: If you were following its agenda, would you even know?

g.title: j42144458->j3510904057
g.text: true

g.title: j42144458->j3510904057
g.text: false

g.title: j1024770786
g.text: At least the human genome is natural.

g.title: j42144458->j1024770786
g.text: true

g.title: j42144458->j1024770786
g.text: false

g.title: j4073870164
g.text: Amir’s caused more sodding injuries than I have.

g.title: j28515795
g.text: She thinks you’ll lose control.

g.title: j4050095683
g.text: I never said that.

g.title: j3173608801
g.text: As opposed to following the agenda of a twisty little double helix of nucleotides? You know, that thing humans have done since they started walking upright?

g.title: j3359445033
g.text: The likes of Viktor Vodyanoi - and what kind of sobriquet is THAT to choose for yourself - justify their backward views by claiming they are ‘natural’. Biological fundamentalism. Man as the mirror of the Divine and all of that.

g.title: j824238930
g.text: But Amir is sweet and a bit ditzy, isn’t he? Amir doesn’t have teeth that could gnaw open a tin of rations. So nobody sees Amir as a bomb waiting to go off.

g.title: j220985153
g.text: +10 Chemistry

g.title: j3008252982
g.text: Some people think humanity is sacred. People like Viktor. I’m the ultimate blasphemy in his eyes. Infected, shameless and female.

g.title: j2920804609
g.text: “Me not do bidding of microscopic tyrant! Me human being. Me special! Find mate. Reproduce. Protect territory. Ug.”

g.title: j2514133886
g.text: But we’ve been unnatural from the moment we started banging rocks together. Language is a virus, mate. Being human is the blank slate we get to scribble on, not the primal Eden we were kicked out of.

g.title: j1982333550
g.text: Well. Except Quincy.

g.title: j2227167520
g.text: The Techrot could hijack your mind and you wouldn’t know it.

g.title: j2202612756
g.text: I’ve seen it absorb entire MOONS, Eleanor!

g.title: j3440369935
g.text: I mean… yes. You’re right. There are parasites that do that.

g.title: j1901364956
g.text: And what’s so bloody wonderful about being an unabsorbed moon? Why is the Infested version not an improvement?

g.title: j1052964379
g.text: But what if it’s not a parasite? What if it’s a symbiote?

g.title: j2206685544
g.text: Oh no! A lump of indifferent space rock that could have drifted aimlessly for another few millennia is suddenly alive and interesting! What a catastrophe!

g.title: j403545694
g.text: You don’t know what you’re talking about. When someone’s lost to the Infestation, they are LOST. Completely unrecognizable.

g.title: j2108631901
g.text: I understand that you need to try to accept what you've become. You're facing an impossible challenge.

g.title: j2432035907
g.text: It’s the exact same bullshit Viktor’s crew come out with. Sentimental clinging on to whatever something USED to be.

g.title: j209076691
g.text: I don’t know if you’re trying to provoke me, but I’ve had to fight for my life against these things. Sometimes you can make out the bits that used to be human. Heads and feet just sticking out of the mass.

g.title: j1794500524
g.text: Either hate what you've become or embrace it. And something tells me you're someone who learned to give up hating themselves a long time ago.

g.title: j3959077190
g.text: As if being primordial was the same as being perfect.

g.title: j2671807523
g.text: It’s not a symbiote. It doesn’t CARE what you want. It’s not here to help. It’s an aggressive cancer of a lifeform that only wants to make everything else into itself.

g.title: j2279038320
g.text: But these demons in your blood are NOT your friends. The best you can do is keep them on a tight leash, Eleanor. Trust. Me.

g.title: j1610426008
g.text: Remind me, what are your Warframes made of again?

g.title: j1620702328
g.text: You think I don't?

g.title: j2317760653
g.text: Infested human beings.

g.title: j3929477543
g.text: Do you have any idea what it takes to keep the rage in check? Do you know what the price of this outward serenity is?

g.title: j4165739497
g.text: But their Infestation was shaped and controlled, wasn’t it?

g.title: j2842957157
g.text: If you see me meditating, I'm not communing with the great cosmic cabbage. I'm cooling down the sodding reactor core.

g.title: j4228695550
g.text: Just like the Infestation that’s in me now.

g.title: j1308043799
g.text: There's SO much I could do and DON'T. Places I could take this... stuff... that you haven't even considered.

g.title: j1648753635
g.text: Which means someone, somewhere had the guts to stop thinking of the Infestation as a brainless monster and start looking at what it could become.

g.title: j719802663
g.text: I could walk into their DREAMS. And they wouldn't even know I'd been there.

g.title: j1457063835
g.text: Oh, you did NOT just describe Ballas as ‘having guts’.

g.title: j3542029976
g.text: So… do you think you’re becoming more yourself, not less?

g.title: j1425913989
g.text: +20 Chemistry

g.title: j729001062
g.text: +10 Chemistry

g.title: j2946077916
g.text: +20 Chemistry

g.title: j3076329731
g.text: Well. This has been an interesting, if uncouth, exchange of views. I had a lovely time. Let's do it again.

g.title: j552750742
g.text: You know, you’re getting quite emotional. We should finish this conversation another time.

g.title: j1798624117
g.text: The last time I got hit with a biochemical sledgehammer that left me sprawled on a couch for half the day and had people whispering behind my back that I was turning into a monster, it was called ‘puberty’.
